                     <join result="offenceVictim" targOrder="Y" targets="t18180218-120-off642 t18180218-120-victim757"></join>
                  </persName>
            .</p>
               <p>CHARLES KESOLEY. I belong to the Stamp Office. On the 17th of January, between ten and eleven o'clock at night, I was opposite Mr. Webber's shop, and saw the prisoner take the lard from the window. I followed him to Great Pulteney-street, he then threw it down, and I seized him. I am sure he is the man.</p>
               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t18180218-120-person758">
                  JAMES 
                  EVANS
               <interp inst="t18180218-120-person758" type="surname" value="EVANS"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18180218-120-person758" type="given" value="JAMES"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18180218-120-person758" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                  </persName>
            . I was in the shop, and saw a man walking about. After I was served I went out- I saw the prisoner snatch the lard and run away- the gentleman followed him. I saw him throw it away. I am sure he is the man.</p>
               <p>JOHN WEBBER. I am a <rs id="t18180218-120-viclabel644" type="occupation">cheesemonger</rs>
                  <join result="persNameOccupation" targOrder="Y" targets="t18180218-120-victim757 t18180218-120-viclabel644"></join>, and live in <placeName id="t18180218-120-crimeloc645">Gower-street</placeName>
                  <interp inst="t18180218-120-crimeloc645" type="placeName" value="Gower-street"></interp>
                  <interp inst="t18180218-120-crimeloc645" type="type" value="crimeLocation"></interp>
                  <join result="offencePlace" targOrder="Y" targets="t18180218-120-off642 t18180218-120-crimeloc645"></join>. The lard is mine.</p>
               <p>Prisoner's Defence. I picked it up.</p>
